[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So right now you\'re looking at my at home podcasting setup that is actually completely controlled by this one little device I have here sitting on my desk and it\'s all touchscreen so I can actually switch over to like a third camera angle or my first camera angle right here. And the crazy thing is all'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of this is 4K resolution and I\'m recording high-quality podcast audio right into my switcher. And we also use a variation of this at Anderson Studios in Las Vegas where we record our Think Media podcast. So today I want to show'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you how we\'ve adopted a 4K podcasting workflow with live switching and recording all in 4K resolution by using products from Yolo Live which partnered with us on today\'s video. So let\'s just explain what we\'re recording with for'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this video today and both me at my workstation today and Kyle at his house has the exact same setup and we\'re going to show you some b-roll from both of the distinct setups. So for our main cameras we\'re using the Yolo Cam S7s. This is a'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '4K Micro Four Thirds mirrorless style camera from Yolo Live and on the front of those cameras we have Yolo Live\'s 18 mm lens attached. Now it\'s a Micro Four Thirds mount so it\'s more going to act'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like a 32 or 35 mm lens would typically. So kind of like a mid-shot that we\'re using for this video on both of our cameras. So that\'s our main camera angle right here in my studio and then camera B is actually that exact same setup over'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here to the right side. And the reason why I love these cameras so much are because they\'re made out of an aluminum body that acts as a heat sink so it pulls heat away from the internals of the camera making it so this camera is'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'literally never going to overheat on you for longer recordings or streams. And then I actually just turned on a third camera over here for fun. This is their Yolo Cam S3. So this is their $200 little webcam that just plugs right into'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the Yolo Box Extreme as well and I can control all three of these cameras all at the same time. And if you want this build to be as budget as possible the S3s honestly make for a really nice and lightweight setup for podcasting and live streams and they\'re super'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'affordable. Now all of these cameras could connect to the YoloBox via USB ports, which allows you to actually control the cameras and configure them for all of their settings like white balance and shutter speed. All of those things you can actually control right'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there from YoloBox or you could plug them into your computer to manually set all of those camera settings. And then the two S7s also have an HDMI output. So, for this video, I\'m running HDMI cables from my S7s directly into the'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'YoloBox and then the YoloCam S3 is plugged in via USB. Now, if you\'re curious about more specs of these cameras, we\'ve done dedicated reviews on the channel of the S7 and the S3. We love them as webcams, but also they\'re'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'great studio cameras or podcasting cameras. Anybody who wants to record content in an indoor environment can leverage these cameras and they\'re also great cuz they\'re never going to overheat. Now, the thing that all of these cameras are plugged into is just'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sitting on my desk right below this camera and it\'s called the YoloBox Extreme and I\'ve done a review about it on this channel that you can check out down in the description below. And basically, what this is is an all-in-one touchscreen switcher and recording'

[02:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'device, but also you can live stream directly from it because it\'s essentially a computer as well and it can handle all of your graphics overlays and processing. And it\'s also an audio mixer that you can bring different audio'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'inputs and mix all of your audio channels. This thing is actually insane and can do so much. So, with just a touch of a button, I can switch different camera angles. So, all I\'m doing right here is I\'ll just look down, switch over to camera three, switch back to camera one. I\'ve also built some like'

[03:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'custom scenes if I want to go side by side. So, if I had like a guest I was podcasting with, I could put us side by side and customize these frames like a hundred different ways. There\'s so many different formats and presets that you'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can use to control different scenes. And if I wanted to invite a remote guest into my podcast, you can actually just generate a link right here from the YoloBox and send it to a guest and they can join in my studio instantly from one'

[03:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'link. Just click the link, join in the studio and then they\'ll pop up in here as a camera feed and then I can add them into the show right from my switcher. You can also add a variety of media inputs or even web pages if you wanted'

[03:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to browse, like I made a little picture-in-picture effect right here, which is cool. I can browse the internet and have my camera as an input. Or this is cool, like directly from the YoloBox, I\'m actually scrolling this webpage right now. So this is our five stages of'

[04:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'YouTube success webpage that I\'m navigating directly from the YoloBox. Like I\'m actually browsing the internet on a switcher, which is wild. I could refresh the page right now if there\'s more information I wanted to load. I can'

