VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually like take this quiz that\'s loading up here. How many videos do I post per month? I post kind of weekly at this point. And I can actually interact with this webpage from the touchscreen interface, which I\'ve literally never'

[04:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'seen that before on another switcher product. If I wanted to bring a little lower third graphic, there\'s like a Craig Pruitt Thing Media graphic that I just made, but you can customize all of these to whatever your preference is would be. So yeah, it handles all of'

[04:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your graphics processing as well. And one of my favorite features by far with the YoloBox Extreme is a feature for auto switching, which is called video follows audio. So you can manually select different audio and camera feeds'

[04:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to pair with each other so that if your guest is on camera one and is speaking through a specific microphone, you can tell the YoloBox to automatically switch the camera angle every time that person speaks to their appropriate camera'

[05:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'angle. And let\'s say you and your guest start talking at the same time, you can actually create a scene that allows for the YoloBox to have like a side-by-side view if it senses both people are speaking at the time. This is such a cool feature. We actually tested this at'

[05:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Anderson Studios when Nate and I were doing a podcast episode together, and Kyle took some behind-the-scenes footage of him just like sitting back on Instagram, just scrolling through Instagram as the podcast was automatically switching with this video'

[05:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'follows audio feature. And it even works when you have remote guests, and we showcase a bit more of these auto switching features, too, in our YoloBox Extreme review if you want to check that out. And then for audio, there\'s lots of different ways you can bring audio into'

[05:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the YoloBox. For this video, I actually just wanted to try one of the simplest methods I\'ve ever tried, which is I\'m using the most affordable podcasting microphone I have. This is the FIFINE AM8. It\'s like a $50 podcast mic, and it has a USB-C output. And I just plug that'

[06:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'directly into the USB-C input of the YoloBox, and it\'s This is the audio that you\'re getting. It sounds fantastic. It sounds like podcast-level audio. It sounds like I\'m using like an XLR interface or a RodeCaster, but I don\'t'

[06:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have to do that. I\'m just plugging a simple USB microphone directly into the YoloBox and capturing this level of audio. So, that\'s how I have this tech setup in my home office to record this kind of multi-cam podcast set. But, let'

