VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Kyle is using the same simple beginner-friendly setup plugging these cameras in to a high-quality podcast studio with professional lighting, and everything is looking equally as crispy. What\'s great about the YoloBox 2 is it'

[07:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'receives different kinds of audio inputs. So, for this build, we\'re actually using a Rodecaster and running all of the audio directly from these sure SM7B microphones directly from their XLR ports. We\'re plugging those'

[08:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'into the Rodecaster, and then with the Rodecaster\'s USB-C output, we plug that directly into the USB-C slot of YoloBox, and we\'re capturing high-quality audio, and we can adjust all of our manual faders and effects and processing from'

[08:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'our audio mixing console and pair that with what\'s happening inside of YoloBox. And there\'s also 3.5 mm audio you could input as well as HDMI sources. So, if we were using like our Sony FX3s with our audio top handles, we can select those'

[08:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cameras as an HDMI source to capture audio that way. There are a couple of accessories you might want to add to your kit if you\'re wanting to build out your set up fully. So, the first thing would be a YoloBox Extreme Cage. So, this is an awesome cage that allows you'

[08:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to mount the YoloBox in some different ways, but also has some nice cable clamps so that you\'re not putting too much tension on your HDMI cables or audio cables. These are some really helpful safety clamps, and there\'s also some cold shoe mounting ports as well as'

[08:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some quarter-20 threads all throughout the body if you want to mount some additional accessories. If you\'re ever doing really long cable runs because this is not an SDI switcher, you might want to look at grabbing some HDMI fiber cables. And so, these are just really'

[09:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'high-quality HDMI cables that can run for longer lengths and still maintain cable integrity. So, if you\'re ever having like signal dropouts and your YoloBox is super far away from your cameras and you\'re using really cheap'

[09:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'long HDMI cables, that can be an issue, but having HDMI fiber cables could be a helpful fix. Okay, so I know this might feel a little bit complex, but honestly, at its core, it is really simple. It\'s It\'s a couple of cameras running into'

[09:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one switching device that\'s also a recorder, and a computer, and a live streaming device. The YoloBox Extreme really is the core and the brain of what makes this all possible. And then adding in these YoloCam S7s or even some S3s'

[09:47] [scene:talk]
